        <updateDate>2020-04-01T18:01:23Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Never Again Act</b></p> <p>This bill requires that excepted federal and District of Columbia public employees who must perform work during a lapse in appropriations (i.e., a government shutdown) be paid, at their standard rate of pay, on scheduled pay dates.</p> <p>Under current law, such employees must be paid at the earliest possible date after the lapse in appropriations ends. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
